CatDescriptText: Two men in overcoats watch as fire fighters attempt to save a burning two story home.  Ladders and hoses lead into the windows of the house, which is smoking from the attic window.  In front are two fire trucks and the fire chief's car, a 1941-42 Buick sedan with "Bureau of Fire C3 Chief River ..." painted on the driver's side door.
TitMainTitle: Fire fighters putting out fire in two-story brick house on hillside, with spectators on hilltop in background, and car from Bureau of Fire, C-3, Chief--River Patrol in foreground
